      "content": "# `gpu.bundle` and render-bundle replay\n\nBundles are explicit. Record static commands once, replay them inside a frame pass, and keep dynamic draws outside the bundle.\n\n```ts\nconst scene = gpu.target({ format: \"rgba16float\", depth: true });\nconst staticScene = gpu.bundle({ target: scene }, (b) => {\n  b.draw(floor);\n  b.draw(walls);\n});\n\ngpu.frame.loop((f) => {\n  f.pass({ target: scene }, (p) => {\n    p.bundles(staticScene);\n    p.draw(player);\n  });\n});\n```\n\nR3 staleness: a bundle freezes commands and bind groups, not buffer contents. `draw.set({ fog: 0.2 })` is safe because JS values write in-place. `draw.set({ tex: otherTexture })` changes resource identity and stales the bundle; replay detects this in dev and tells you to re-record.\n\nPing-pong with bundles uses two recorded bundles, one for each stable resource identity:\n\n```ts\nconst even = gpu.bundle({ target: ping.write }, (b) => { sim.set({ src: ping.read }); b.draw(sim); });\nping.swap();\nconst odd = gpu.bundle({ target: ping.write }, (b) => { sim.set({ src: ping.read }); b.draw(sim); });\nping.swap();\n\ngpu.frame.loop((f) => {\n  f.pass({ target: ping.write }, (p) => p.bundles(gpu.frameCount % 2 ? odd : even));\n  ping.swap();\n});\n```\n\n## Ownership and performance defaults\n\n- WGSL is the source of truth. Declare every `@group/@binding` in the shader and bind by name with `set()`.\n- JS values passed to `set()` are lib-owned and are written in-place (R1/R2), so animated uniforms do not recreate bind groups.\n- Resources (`Uniform`, storage buffers, textures, targets, samplers, claimed bind groups) are user-owned; vgpu only binds their identity.\n- Time is explicit JS (`gpu.time`, `gpu.deltaTime`, `gpu.frameCount`). Resolution lives on targets (`target.size`, `target.texelSize`).\n"
