      "content": "# `Uniform`\n\nRing-0 escape hatch for a user-owned uniform buffer. Prefer `set({ value })` for ordinary values; use `Uniform` when one write must feed many draws or when you need byte-level control.\n\n```ts\nimport { Uniform } from \"vgpu/core\";\nconst camera = new Uniform(gpu.device, { size: 64, label: \"camera\" });\nconst cube = gpu.draw({ shader: LIT_WGSL });\ncube.set({ camera });\ncamera.write(viewProjection);\n```\n\nBecause `camera` is a resource, ownership is user-owned from the first `set()` (R1). vgpu only binds it; you own writes and lifetime.\n"
